              "id": "1CoQkiwT5DLKogENcDSXtN",
              "type": "authorPaper",
              "text": "Model-Based Discrimination Analysis: A Position Paper",
              "articleLocation": "pdfs/FairWare2018-3qfVb2GCei41clAYgZuwc/3Qk82mYhyMsXIJACPsFG3d/ECdfHqxCyJwZEvHWZ5xEO.pdf",
              "extraLocations": [],
              "authorNames": "Qusai Ramadan (University of Koblenz-Landau), Amir Shayan Ahmadian (University of Koblenz-Landau), Daniel Strüber (University of Koblenz-Landau), Jan Jürjens (University of Koblenz-Landau), Steffen Staab (University of Koblenz-Landau)",
              "abstract": "Decision-making software may exhibit biases due to hidden dependencies between protected characteristics and the data used as input for making decisions. To uncover such dependencies, we propose the development of a framework to support discrimination analysis during the system design phase, based on system models and available data.",
              "searchText": "2018 ACM/IEEE International Workshop on Software Fairness FairWare 2018 Model-Based Discrimination Analysis: A Position Paper 1521481718188 Qusai Ramadan University of Koblenz-Landau qramadan@uni-koblenz.de Amir Shayan Ahmadian University of Koblenz-Landau ahmadian@uni-koblenz.de Daniel Strüber University of Koblenz-Landau strueber@uni-koblenz.de Jan Jürjens University of Koblenz-Landau juerjens@uni-koblenz.de Steffen Staab University of Koblenz-Landau staab@uni-koblenz.de Software Fairness UML Model-based Analysis Decision-making software may exhibit biases due to hidden dependencies between protected characteristics and the data used as input for making decisions. To uncover such dependencies, we propose the development of a framework to support discrimination analysis during the system design phase, based on system models and available data.",
