              "authorNames": "Hélène de Ribaupierre (Cardiff University), Kathryn Jones (Cardiff University), Fernando Loizides (Cardiff University), Yulia Cherdantseva (Cardiff University)",
              "abstract": "Multiple studies show that women are under-represented in almost all of fields of Science, Technology, Engineering and Maths (STEM). This gender gap is also present at higher education institutions in both student numbers and academic staff. A range of measures could be implemented to tackle this issue. In this position paper, we outline the measures that the School of Computer Sciences and Informatics of Cardiff University, UK, implemented over the past years, to foster a culture in which women could excel. Then, we discuss the measures that we plan to implement in future in order to increase the number of women both among students and academic staff.",
              "searchText": "2018 ACM/IEEE 1st International Workshop on Gender Equality in Software Engineering GE 2018 Towards Gender Equality in Software Engineering: The NSA Approach 1521384082105 Hélène de Ribaupierre Cardiff University deribaupierreH@cardiff.ac.uk Kathryn Jones Cardiff University JonesK90@cardiff.ac.uk Fernando Loizides Cardiff University loizidesF@cardiff.ac.uk Yulia Cherdantseva Cardiff University CherdantsevaYV@cardiff.ac.uk Gender Equality Education Software Engineering Computer Science STEM Multiple studies show that women are under-represented in almost all of fields of Science, Technology, Engineering and Maths (STEM). This gender gap is also present at higher education institutions in both student numbers and academic staff. A range of measures could be implemented to tackle this issue. In this position paper, we outline the measures that the School of Computer Sciences and Informatics of Cardiff University, UK, implemented over the past years, to foster a culture in which women could excel. Then, we discuss the measures that we plan to implement in future in order to increase the number of women both among students and academic staff.",
