              "articleLocation": "pdfs/GE2018-5lsO9wN3fGslwPufsqk9fU/1wGZL7pZeM2RgXvjAnI5BH/2yYqS98aZR7Oy4bfPyCspo.pdf",
              "extraLocations": [],
              "authorNames": "Lori Clarke (University of Massachusetts), Lori Pollock (University of Delaware), Jane Stout (Computing Research Association), Carla Ellis (Duke University), Tracy Camp (Colorado School of Mines), Betsy Bizot (Computing Research Association), Kathryn S. McKinley (Google)",
              "abstract": "The Committee on the Status of Women in Computing is an action-oriented committee of the Computing Research Association with the goal of taking positive action to increase the number and success of women in the Computer Science and Engineering research pipeline. This paper describes CRA-Ws major programs and highlights some of their impacts as demonstrated through evaluation.",
              "searchText": "2018 ACM/IEEE 1st International Workshop on Gender Equality in Software Engineering GE 2018 Improving Diversity in Computing Research: An Overview of CRA-W Activities 1521380275435 Lori Clarke University of Massachusetts clarke@cs.umass.edu Lori Pollock University of Delaware pollock@udel.edu Jane Stout Computing Research Association jane@cra.org Carla Ellis Duke University carla@cs.duke.edu Tracy Camp Colorado School of Mines tcamp@mines.edu Betsy Bizot Computing Research Association bizot@cra.org Kathryn S. McKinley Google ksmckinley@google.com CS Ph.D. research pipeline CRA-W programs The Committee on the Status of Women in Computing is an action-oriented committee of the Computing Research Association with the goal of taking positive action to increase the number and success of women in the Computer Science and Engineering research pipeline. This paper describes CRA-Ws major programs and highlights some of their impacts as demonstrated through evaluation.",
              "pageNumber": 41,
