              "id": "qLZSi1d7KCy8HericIxlx",
              "type": "authorPaper",
              "text": "Designing Control Software for Robot Swarms: Software Engineering for the Development of Automatic Design Methods",
              "articleLocation": "pdfs/RoSE2018-6kiuVCU6NN0fA85PxfP07x/EWmht6VppuwewEj1EHwx8/55a9DmzRQinAzjC6Avoz09.pdf",
              "extraLocations": [],
              "authorNames": "Darko Bozhinoski (Université Libre de Bruxelles), Mauro Birattari (Université Libre de Bruxelles)",
              "abstract": "Over the past decade, swarm robotics has emerged as a promising engineering discipline. In this paper, we discuss the current research challenges and state-of-the-art in automatic design methods for swarm control software. This subject has recently received increasing attention from the swarm robotics community.We make a contribution towards the debate by proposing two lines of research from a software engineering point of view.",
              "searchText": "2018 ACM/IEEE 1st International Workshop on Robotics Software Engineering RoSE 2018 Designing Control Software for Robot Swarms: Software Engineering for the Development of Automatic Design Methods 1521455854013 Darko Bozhinoski Université Libre de Bruxelles darko.bozhinoski@ulb.ac.be Mauro Birattari Université Libre de Bruxelles mbiro@ulb.ac.be swarm robotics software engineering design by optimization Over the past decade, swarm robotics has emerged as a promising engineering discipline. In this paper, we discuss the current research challenges and state-of-the-art in automatic design methods for swarm control software. This subject has recently received increasing attention from the swarm robotics community.We make a contribution towards the debate by proposing two lines of research from a software engineering point of view.",
