              "abstract": "We report on the advances in this sixth edition of the JUnit tool competitions. This year the contest introduces new benchmarks to assess the performance of JUnit testing tools on different types of real-world software projects. Following on the statistical analyses from the past contest work, we have extended it with the combined tools performance aiming to beat the human made tests. Overall, the 6th competition evaluates four automated JUnit testing tools taking as baseline human written test cases for the selected benchmark projects. The paper details the modifications performed to the methodology and provides full results of the competition.",
              "searchText": "2018 ACM/IEEE 11th International Workshop on Search-Based Software Testing SBST 2018 Java Unit Testing Tool Competition - Sixth Round 1521195457912 Urko Rueda Molina Universitat Politècnica de València urueda@pros.upv.es Fitsum Kifetew Fondazione Bruno Kessler kifetew@fbk.eu Annibale Panichella University of Luxembourg and Delft University of Technology annibale.panichella@uni.lu tool competition benchmark mutation testing automation unit testing Java statistical analysis combined performance We report on the advances in this sixth edition of the JUnit tool competitions. This year the contest introduces new benchmarks to assess the performance of JUnit testing tools on different types of real-world software projects. Following on the statistical analyses from the past contest work, we have extended it with the combined tools performance aiming to beat the human made tests. Overall, the 6th competition evaluates four automated JUnit testing tools taking as baseline human written test cases for the selected benchmark projects. The paper details the modifications performed to the methodology and provides full results of the competition.",
