              "id": "7sXGjvvLDCuVKGwlnftoXk",
              "type": "authorPaper",
              "text": "Timing Verification of Component-Based Vehicle Software with Rubus-ICE: End-User's Experience",
              "articleLocation": "pdfs/SQUADE2018-52YkchboRqqdpLhjNfFOjE/1egreI0Xy5coGIKhPLsnaj/4xX8TBDuYX3wadvpwr3yS9.pdf",
              "extraLocations": [],
              "authorNames": "Saad Mubeen (Mälardalen University), Mattias Gålnander (Arcticus Systems), Alessio Bucaioni (Arcticus Systems), John Lundbäck (Arcticus Systems), Kurt-Lennart Lundbäck (Arcticus Systems)",
              "abstract": "This paper discusses an end-user's experiences of utilizing timing analysis tools to verify predictability of distributed embedded systems in the vehicle industry. The analysis tools are plug-ins for an industrial tool suite, namely Rubus-ICE, that is based on the principles of model-based engineering (MBE) and component-based software engineering (CBSE). These plug-ins implement various state-of-the-art timing analyses including response-time analysis and end-to-end data-path analysis. The experiences discussed in this paper provide a useful feedback in terms of usability and validity of assumptions to the tools provider as well as to the academia.",
              "searchText": "2018 ACM/IEEE 1st International Workshop on Software Qualities and Their Dependencies SQUADE 2018 Timing Verification of Component-Based Vehicle Software with Rubus-ICE: End-User's Experience 1522920505757 Saad Mubeen Mälardalen University saad.mubeen@mdh.se Mattias Gålnander Arcticus Systems mattias.galnander@arcticus-systems.com Alessio Bucaioni Arcticus Systems alessio.bucaioni@arcticus-systems.com John Lundbäck Arcticus Systems john.lundback@arcticus-systems.com Kurt-Lennart Lundbäck Arcticus Systems kurt.lundback@arcticus-systems.com Automotive software End-to-end timing analysis CBSE MBE This paper discusses an end-user's experiences of utilizing timing analysis tools to verify predictability of distributed embedded systems in the vehicle industry. The analysis tools are plug-ins for an industrial tool suite, namely Rubus-ICE, that is based on the principles of model-based engineering (MBE) and component-based software engineering (CBSE). These plug-ins implement various state-of-the-art timing analyses including response-time analysis and end-to-end data-path analysis. The experiences discussed in this paper provide a useful feedback in terms of usability and validity of assumptions to the tools provider as well as to the academia.",
